  "prompt": "What are some alternatives to yelp in India?",
  "response": "In India, several alternatives to Yelp can help users find restaurants, cafes, and other local services. Here are some popular options:\n\n1. **Zomato**: One of the most widely used platforms for discovering restaurants, Zomato provides user reviews, menus, and photos. It also offers a food delivery service.\n\n2. **Swiggy**: Primarily known as a food delivery platform, Swiggy also includes restaurant reviews and ratings, making it a handy option for discovering new dining spots.\n\n3. **Google Maps**: While primarily a navigation tool, Google Maps features user reviews and ratings for restaurants and other local businesses, making it a popular choice for finding nearby places.\n\n4. **Tripadvisor**: Known for travel-related content, Tripadvisor includes extensive user reviews and ratings for restaurants, attractions, and hotels across India.\n\n5. **Dineout**: This platform focuses on dining out, offering restaurant recommendations, online reservations, and various deals or discounts at various eateries.\n\n6. **BookMyShow**: While primarily a ticketing platform for movies and events, BookMyShow also includes restaurant recommendations, especially in metropolitan areas.\n\n7. **Justdial**: A local search engine, Justdial gives users access to listings and reviews for various services, including restaurants, hotels, and more.\n\n8. **EazyDiner**: This platform offers restaurant reservations, recommendations, and exclusive deals in various cities across India.\n\n9. **Nearbuy**: This app offers discounts and deals on local experiences, including dining, and features user reviews and ratings.\n\n10. **MagicPin**: A platform that provides users with deals and cashback for shopping and dining at local businesses, along with user reviews.\n\nThese platforms can help users in India with discovering new places to eat and get services, often with user-generated reviews and recommendations.",
